Shougang Park, a steel mill that was turned into a cultural and sports complex in western Beijing, became the subject of worldwide attention during the Beijing 2022 Winter Olympics. How many people know the relocation of Shougang's operations in 2005, and the subsequent transformation of the Beijing site, are part of an ongoing anti-pollution campaign? In episode one of "A Low-Carbon China", we look at similar efforts being made by the Chinese government to reduce carbon emissions and the push toward creating a sustainable future globally.